##Zhong Nanshan: This is a priority!

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

With the arrival of the early spring season, the influenza has also entered a peak season. In the new coronavirus pneumonia epidemic, academician Zhong Nanshan recently declared: the influenza and new pneumonia to distinguish between the two categories of patients is an urgent matter.

Why is it so important to distinguish between influenza and new coronary pneumonia?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhong Nanshan

It is imperative to distinguish between influenza and new pneumonia

On the 23rd, academician Zhong Nanshan stressed the importance of distinguishing between influenza and new pneumonia during a remote consultation with the Guangdong medical team supporting Jingzhou in Guangzhou. Zhong Nanshan said, the key to prevention and control now is to separate the two diseases: "there is an influenza pandemic in the United States, and the number of cases is much higher than the number of new cases of pneumonia. China has this [ flu ] situation, and it is imperative to distinguish between the two. "

Meanwhile, Zhong Nanshan revealed that China's State Drug Administration has now approved several drugs, one of which is a reagent on how to identify influenza, new pneumonia and parainfluenza. Zhong Nanshan says bluntly: "This is the key job. ".

Why is it urgent to distinguish between influenza and new coronavirus pneumonia? An immunologist, who asked not to be named, explained to Chinanews.com: Emerging Infectious Diseases pneumonia is a class a infectious disease, and influenza is a Class C infectious disease.

As the current flu season approaches, the experts make clear: "If you do not distinguish between the two, especially the two as a new coronavirus pneumonia for centralized treatment, will greatly increase the risk of cross-infection. "

However, the difficulty of distinguishing between the two diseases is still in the detection and diagnosis. "For now, the best way to tell the difference between the two diseases is still to do an etiological test or an immunological test, commonly known as a nucleic acid test, " he explains. However, the sequences detected by the two methods are different. NCP is mainly detected by NPV, and influenza is detected by influenza virus.

However, because Emerging Infectious Diseases is a type of pneumonia, there are still gaps in the diagnosis. Expert Analysis: "NEW PNEUMONIA NUCLEIC ACID test positive rate is relatively low, clinical symptoms are more diverse, so to identify up also need to accumulate experience. "

What are the differences between influenza and new coronary pneumonia?

The peak season for influenza outbreaks is winter and early spring. How can we tell the difference between influenza and NCP in the context of the NCP epidemic?

Wang Quan, director of the Emergency Department of the Beijing Children's Hospital affiliated to the Capital University of Medical Sciences, told a news conference held by the National Health and Welfare Commission on February 1, the comparison was made from four aspects: the source of the disease, the time of onset, the symptoms and the susceptible population.

First, from the pathogenic point of view, Wang Quan clear, influenza is a respiratory infectious disease, caused by influenza virus. COVID-19 pneumonia is also an infectious disease with a well established epidemiological history, caused by infection with a new coronavirus.

Second, the timing of the onset of the two diseases is not the same. Wang Quan explained that influenza may occur throughout the year, but the peak season is mainly winter and spring. The new coronavirus pneumonia from the present, then is 2019 the winter newly onset disease.

In addition, the experts added, the incubation period of the two diseases is slightly different: "new pneumonia in patients with the incubation period is basically 14 days, a few will be longer; but the incubation period of influenza is generally within a week, more than 10 days of incubation is rare. "

From the clinical symptoms, both diseases accompanied by fever phenomenon. "The flu has a very pronounced fever, often a high fever, lasting three to five days. The main symptoms of NCP include fever, cough, weakness and even vomiting, abdominal pain and diarrhea, " Wang said.

The immunologist said that while both are respiratory disease, the flu is upper respiratory tract infection, with symptoms such as runny nose and bronchial irritation, and lower respiratory tract infection, the expression appears inflammation in the lung, the patient often gives priority to with dry cough, and have the circumstance of breathing difficulty.

Finally, from the point of view of susceptible groups, Wang Quan pointed out that both influenza and NCP belong to the general susceptibility groups, especially children under 2 years old, elderly people over 65 years old, obese people, pregnant women, and patients with immunosuppression, are At high risk for the flu. In addition, in the present case, NCP is more severe in the elderly and in patients with chronic underlying diseases and may even be fatal.

Flu VS new pneumonia

Which is scarier?

As a Emerging Infectious Diseases, the new crown pneumonia epidemic is on the rise. As of 2400 hours on February 23,31 provinces and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps had reported 49,824 confirmed cases, including 9,915 severe cases, 24,734 discharged cases, 25,92 deaths, and 77,150 confirmed cases.

Flu, by contrast, is no less dangerous. According to the World Health Organization in 2019, influenza is estimated to cause 1 billion cases worldwide each year, including 3 million to 5 million severe cases, and between 290,000 and 650,000 flu related respiratory disease deaths.

So, the flu is worse than the new pneumonia?

"In terms of infectiousness and mortality, it is difficult to tell which is more serious, " experts said, adding that it was too early to assess the severity of the new pneumonia epidemic. The reason why it is directly defined as a category B infectious disease and management according to Category A infectious disease, because it is a Emerging Infectious Diseases, its incidence path is not clear, so control measures higher than influenza.

But experts say the public need not panic about the flu. "compared to NCP, we have been dealing with influenza for a long time, and we know a lot about the characteristics of the disease and the basic immunity of patients with this disease. "

Experts say flu is treatable for most people, such as Oseltamivir for swine flu, which does not require hospitalisation as long as it is treated appropriately.

"What's more, China already has sophisticated technology for treating influenza, which can adapt the vaccine production line to produce seasonal flu vaccines based on the flu strain. There is also a cure for flu, so there is no need to panic about the flu."

In contrast, the lack of specific drugs and vaccines has led to the need for hospital treatment for NCP. At the same time, experts also remind, whether it is the flu or new pneumonia, patients need not be nervous but also can not take it lightly: "especially in the case of cold medicine control, if symptoms still need to go to the hospital, and do a good job of preventive measures. "
